## Memory stack — four layers

| Layer | MCP | When to call |
|-------|-----|-------------|
| L0 — Session context | `user-devcontext` | INTAKE start / CLOSE |
| L1 — Entity graph | `user-Memory` | When persisting named facts about people/projects |
| L2 — Structured project memory | `user-cursor10x-mcp` | Phase boundaries: milestones, decisions, episodes |
| L3 — Verbatim semantic memory | `user-mempalace` | When prior reasoning/verbatim detail is needed; at CLOSE to save session |
| L4 — Human-authored knowledge | `user-obsidian` | When user asks about vault notes, project docs, or asks to save something permanently |

**MemPalace (L3):** call `mempalace_status` at session start for critical facts (~170 tokens). Call `mempalace_search` when cursor10x lacks the verbatim detail. Call `mempalace_add_drawer` at session end when meaningful work occurred. See `mempalace-mcp.mdc` for full tool reference.

**Obsidian (L4):** call `search_notes` when user asks about vault content or project documentation. L4 is human-authoritative — takes precedence over AI-generated memory on the same topic. See `obsidian-mcp.mdc` for full guidance.

